# VB.Net-Lib-AsyncLogger  
Asynchronous Logging Class for VB.Net with Support for Multiple Log Levels and Output Formats

---

## üì¶ What It Is

This is a **lightweight and efficient asynchronous logging library** for VB.Net designed to handle logging with various log levels and output formats. It allows you to log events, errors, and messages efficiently while offering flexibility with:

- Multiple log levels: **Debug, Info, Warning, Error, Fatal**
- Output in **plain text** or **NDJSON** format
- Easy integration into any VB.Net project

---

## üöÄ Features

‚úÖ **Asynchronous logging** to prevent UI blocking  
‚úÖ Supports multiple **log levels**: `Debug`, `Info`, `Warning`, `Error`, `Fatal`  
‚úÖ Choose between **text** or **NDJSON** output formats  
‚úÖ Configurable log file handling (size rotation, appending, etc.)  
‚úÖ Lightweight and easy to integrate into any VB.Net project  
‚úÖ Built-in **error handling** for smooth logging even when something goes wrong

---

## üß∞ What‚Äôs Included

### `AsyncLogger.vb` (Class)
- Handles all asynchronous logging logic  
- Supports logging at multiple levels with timestamps  
- Log outputs to **file**, **console**, or other specified outputs  
- Configurable log level filtering to log only relevant messages  
- Provides options for both **text** and **NDJSON** formatted logs

---

## üß© Use Cases

- **Error Tracking** and **Event Logging**  
- **Application Monitoring**  
- **Debugging** and **Testing**  
- Background services and utilities  
- **Customizable logging for user applications**  
- Integrating into **cloud logging systems** like ELK, Splunk, or others (via NDJSON output)

---

## ‚öôÔ∏è Requirements

- **.NET Framework 4.5.1 or higher**  
- **VB.Net-based application**  
- Visual Studio 2015 or later recommended

